# Apply Supabase migrations automatically

When you **add** or **modify** any file in `supabase/migrations/`:

1. **Run the migration** – Execute `npx supabase db push` in the project root (use `;` instead of `&&` in PowerShell).
2. **Do it without asking** – Do not ask the user to run it; run it yourself as part of the same change.
3. **Once per change** – One run after the migration work is done is enough; no need to run it again unless you add or change another migration.

This ensures the database is always in sync with migrations without the user having to remember to run the command.
